# Chapter 4 – Splunk Enterprise Installation

## Objective

The objective of this chapter was to install and configure Splunk Enterprise on the Ubuntu Server virtual machine. Splunk Enterprise serves as the centralized Security Information and Event Management (SIEM) platform responsible for collecting, indexing, searching, and analyzing security events generated throughout the SOC Detection and Monitoring Lab.

---

## Lab Environment

| Component | Configuration |
|----------|---------------|
| Operating System | Ubuntu Server |
| SIEM Platform | Splunk Enterprise 9.4.2 |
| Virtualization Platform | Oracle VirtualBox |
| Ubuntu Hostname | splunk |
| Ubuntu IP Address | 10.10.10.4 |
| Network Type | NAT Network |

---

# Step 1 – Verify Available Disk Space

Before installing Splunk Enterprise, the available disk space on the Ubuntu Server was verified.

### Command

```bash
df -h
```

